  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>I'm Adil Nussipov&mdash;a writer and technologist interested in how tools shape thought, how craft resists automation, and what it means to pay close attention in an age designed to fragment it.</p>
  <p>I've spent time building software products and thinking about the systems underneath them. These essays are where I work things out slowly, in public.</p>
  <p>I'm based in [City]. You can reach me at <a href="mailto:adil@adilnussipov.com">adil@adilnussipov.com</a>.</p>
